---
import PortfolioLayout from '../layouts/PortfolioLayout.astro';
import { GITHUB_URL } from '../consts';
---

<PortfolioLayout
	title="GitHub | ShangLi Zhou"
	description="GitHub profile and project placeholder for ShangLi Zhou."
>
	<section class="page-hero">
		<p class="eyebrow" data-i18n="github.eyebrow">GitHub</p>
		<h1 data-i18n="github.title">README and Project Placeholder</h1>
		<p data-i18n="github.intro">
			This page mirrors the GitHub requirement for the assignment: a profile link, README content,
			and one project entry to replace with a final repository later.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<article class="card readme-card">
			<p class="section-label" data-i18n="github.readmeLabel">README Preview</p>
			<h2 data-i18n="github.readmeTitle">ShangLi Zhou Portfolio</h2>
			<p data-i18n="github.readmeBody">
				A bilingual game developer portfolio built with Astro. It includes individual work,
				team projects, personal documents, LinkedIn, and GitHub links.
			</p>
			<a class="button" href={GITHUB_URL} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" data-i18n="github.openProfile"
				>Open GitHub Profile</a
			>
		</article>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<article class="card">
			<p class="tag" data-i18n="github.projectTag">Project Placeholder</p>
			<h2 data-i18n="github.projectTitle">DFS I Engine Foundation</h2>
			<p data-i18n="github.projectBody">
				A placeholder repository entry for an individual game-engine project. The final GitHub
				project will include source code, build notes, screenshots, and a README describing the
				technical goals.
			</p>
		</article>
	</section>
</PortfolioLayout>
